article.headline: Austin Peay 80, Morehead State 48
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Todd Babington came off the bench to score a season high 25 points as Austin Peay beat Morehead State 80-48 Saturday night. Babington hit eight of 13 shots from the field, including seven 3-pointers. Drake Reed added 19 points for Austin Peay. Austin Peay (17-13, 11-9 Ohio Valley Conference) led 38-23 at the half. Leading 47-29, the Governors went on a 15-0 run to put the game out of reach. Quinton Smith paced the Eagles (4-23, 3-17 OVC) with 16 points. The Governors connected on 10 of 23 of 3-pointers, and outrebounded Morehead State 41-23. The win was head coach David Loos 250th career (250-223) victory at Austin Peay.
